data.bio: Alabama Shakes is an American blues rock band formed in Athens, Alabama in 2009. The band currently consists of lead singer and guitarist Brittany Howard, guitarist Heath Fogg, bassist Zac Cockrell, and drummer Steve Johnson. The group rose to prominence in the early 2010s with their distinctive and soulful roots rock sound.

Inspired and imaginative, Roadwings Entertainment is a passionately creative production company. With offices in Austin, San Francisco, New York City, and Las Vegas, our expert and inventive team brings top tier talent to the art of storytelling. We produce content for all audiences, through a panorama of media, including documentary and feature films, music videos, commercials, web videos, and print photography.

Run the Jewels, also known by the initialism RTJ, is an American hip hop[1][2] supergroup formed in 2013 by rapper/producer El-P and rapper Killer Mike.[3] They released their acclaimed debut studio album, Run the Jewels, as a free digital download in 2013.

Gary Clark Jr.[1] (born February 15, 1984) is an American musician from Austin, Texas.[2][3][4] Dubbed 'The Chosen One', Clark has shared the stage with many legends of rock and roll, including Eric Clapton, B. B. King and the Rolling Stones.[5] He is best known for his fusion of blues, rock and soul music with elements of hip hop.

Rhiannon Giddens is an American musician. She is known as the lead singer, violinist, banjo player and a founding member of the Grammy-winning country, blues and old-time music band Carolina Chocolate Drops.

Moon Taxi is an American indie-progressive rock band based in Nashville, Tennessee. The band was founded in 2006 by Trevor Terndrup, Tommy Putnam, Spencer Thomson, Tyler Ritter, and Wes Bailey while attending Belmont University.
